#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:4
msgid "How to use subtests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:10
msgid ""
"This feature is experimental. Its behavior, particularly how failures are "
"reported, may evolve in future releases. However, the core functionality and "
"usage are considered stable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:12
msgid ""
"pytest allows for grouping assertions within a normal test, known as "
"*subtests*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:14
msgid ""
"Subtests are an alternative to parametrization, particularly useful when the "
"exact parametrization values are not known at collection time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:17
msgid ""
"# content of test_subtest.py\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def test(subtests):\n"
"    for i in range(5):\n"
"        with subtests.test(msg=\"custom message\", i=i):\n"
"            assert i % 2 == 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:27
msgid ""
"Each assertion failure or error is caught by the context manager and "
"reported individually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:29
msgid ""
"$ pytest -q test_subtest.py\n"
"uuuuuF                                                               [100%]\n"
"================================= FAILURES "
"=================================\n"
"_______________________ test [custom message] (i=1) "
"________________________\n"
"\n"
"subtests = <_pytest.subtests.Subtests object at 0xdeadbeef0001>\n"
"\n"
"    def test(subtests):\n"
"        for i in range(5):\n"
"            with subtests.test(msg=\"custom message\", i=i):\n"
">               assert i % 2 == 0\n"
"E               assert (1 % 2) == 0\n"
"\n"
"test_subtest.py:6: AssertionError\n"
"_______________________ test [custom message] (i=3) "
"________________________\n"
"\n"
"subtests = <_pytest.subtests.Subtests object at 0xdeadbeef0001>\n"
"\n"
"    def test(subtests):\n"
"        for i in range(5):\n"
"            with subtests.test(msg=\"custom message\", i=i):\n"
">               assert i % 2 == 0\n"
"E               assert (3 % 2) == 0\n"
"\n"
"test_subtest.py:6: AssertionError\n"
"___________________________________ test "
"___________________________________\n"
"contains 2 failed subtests\n"
"========================= short test summary info "
"==========================\n"
"SUBFAILED[custom message] (i=1) test_subtest.py::test - assert (1 % 2) == 0\n"
"SUBFAILED[custom message] (i=3) test_subtest.py::test - assert (3 % 2) == 0\n"
"FAILED test_subtest.py::test - contains 2 failed subtests\n"
"3 failed, 3 subtests passed in 0.12s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:64
msgid "In the output above:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:66
msgid "Subtest failures are reported as ``SUBFAILED``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:67
msgid ""
"Subtests are reported first and the \"top-level\" test is reported at the "
"end on its own."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:69
msgid ""
"Note that it is possible to use ``subtests`` multiple times in the same "
"test, or even mix and match with normal assertions outside the ``subtests."
"test`` block:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:72
msgid ""
"def test(subtests):\n"
"    for i in range(5):\n"
"        with subtests.test(\"stage 1\", i=i):\n"
"            assert i % 2 == 0\n"
"\n"
"    assert func() == 10\n"
"\n"
"    for i in range(10, 20):\n"
"        with subtests.test(\"stage 2\", i=i):\n"
"            assert i % 2 == 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:87
msgid "See :ref:`parametrize` for an alternative to subtests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:91
msgid "Verbosity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:93
msgid ""
"By default, only **subtest failures** are shown. Higher verbosity levels (:"
"option:`-v`) will also show progress output for **passed** subtests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:95
msgid ""
"It is possible to control the verbosity of subtests by setting :confval:"
"`verbosity_subtests`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:99
msgid "Typing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:101
msgid ""
":class:`pytest.Subtests` is exported so it can be used in type annotations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:103
msgid "def test(subtests: pytest.Subtests) -> None: ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:110
msgid "Parametrization vs Subtests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:112
msgid ""
"While :ref:`traditional pytest parametrization <parametrize>` and "
"``subtests`` are similar, they have important differences and use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:116
msgid "Parametrization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:118
msgid "Happens at collection time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:119
msgid "Generates individual tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:120
msgid "Parametrized tests can be referenced from the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:121
msgid ""
"Plays well with plugins that handle test execution, such as :option:`--last-"
"failed`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:122
msgid "Ideal for decision table testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:125
msgid "Subtests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:127
msgid "Happen during test execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:128
msgid "Are not known at collection time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:129
msgid "Can be generated dynamically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:130
msgid "Cannot be referenced individually from the command line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:131
msgid "Plugins that handle test execution cannot target individual subtests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:132
msgid ""
"An assertion failure inside a subtest does not interrupt the test, letting "
"users see all failures in the same report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:137
msgid ""
"This feature was originally implemented as a separate plugin in `pytest-"
"subtests <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-subtests>`__, but since "
"``9.0`` has been merged into the core."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/subtests.rst:139
msgid ""
"The core implementation should be compatible to the plugin implementation, "
"except it does not contain custom command-line options to control subtest "
"output."
msgstr ""
